---
layout: layouts/base.njk
---

<!-- Hero Section -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="Permacommons" class="hero-logo">
      <h1>Permacommons</h1>
      <p class="hero-tagline">Minding the Future</p>
      <p class="hero-description">Building a permanent home for useful shared resources maintained with AI assistance</p>
      <div class="hero-buttons">
        <a href="https://github.com/permacommons" class="btn btn-primary">View on GitHub</a>
        <a href="/blog/" class="btn btn-secondary">Read Our Blog</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Featured Projects Section -->
<section class="content-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">Featured Projects</h2>
    </div>
    {% from "macros/projects.njk" import project_carousel %}
    {{ project_carousel(projects) }}
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Mission Section -->
<section class="content-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">Our Mission</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Starting with open source software, we are using AI to grow and nurture a permanent commons.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-grid">
      <div class="content-card">
        <p>Permacommons is building a permanent home for useful shared resources that are maintained with AI assistance. We are starting with open source software.</p>

        <p>Our mission is to create a sustainable ecosystem where the amount of human labor scales with the quality of AI systems—as they improve, human effort decreases, but never at the expense of quality, usability, or security.</p>

        <p>Our long-term goal is to sustain compute and human effort through an endowment fund, making the commons truly permanent. But we're taking it one step at a time. The first step is to grow a community that welcomes the responsible use of AI in open source development.</p>

        <p>Currently, the best place to follow our work is <a href="https://github.com/permacommons">on GitHub</a>. We are focusing on simple tools and scripts and will work our way up as the technology improves.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Vision Section -->
<section class="content-section vision-section reduced-padding">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">Our Vision</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">To forge possibility into abundance for all humanity.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-grid">
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Latest From Our Blog</h3>
        <div class="blog-headings">
          {%- for post in collections.posts -%}
            {%- if loop.index <= 3 -%}
          <div class="blog-heading">
            <h4><a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a></h4>
            <p class="blog-post-meta">
              <time datetime="{{ post.date | dateIso }}">{{ post.date | readableDate }}</time>
              {%- if post.data.author -%}
              <span>•</span>
              <span>{{ post.data.author }}</span>
              {%- endif -%}
            </p>
          </div>
            {%- endif -%}
          {%- endfor -%}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Call to Action Section -->
<section class="content-section cta-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">For Open Source Developers</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">Are you looking for a community home for your projects that welcomes the responsible use of AI? <a href="https://github.com/orgs/permacommons/discussions/categories/show-and-tell">Tell us about your project!</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="text-center">
      <a href="https://github.com/orgs/permacommons/discussions" class="btn btn-primary">Join Our Community</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
